column1:
Old-age (65 and older) dependency ratio (per 100 people ages 15-64)
null
Dimension: Demography
Definition: Ratio of the population ages 65 and older to the population ages 15–64, expressed as the number of dependants per 100 people of working age (ages 15–64).
Source: UNDESA (2019b). World Population Prospects: The 2019 Revision. New York. https://population.un.org/wpp/. Accessed 19 June 2019.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development

column1: a: Includes Christmas Island, Cocos (Keeling) Islands and Norfolk Island.
e: Includes Abkhazia and South Ossetia.
g: Includes Agalega, Rodrigues and Saint Brandon.
i: Includes Svalbard and Jan Mayen Islands.
l: Includes Canary Islands, Ceuta and Melilla.
